2002年，在他的[[現代藝術博物館|MoMA]]回顧展的同一年，李希特受委託設計 [[科隆主教座堂|科隆主教座堂]] 設計彩色[[花窗玻璃|花窗玻璃]]。2007年8月正式揭幕完成後的彩色玻璃窗。它是利由抽象拼貼的方式，約11,500個像素般的正方形玻璃，一共72種顏色，對稱地、隨機地排列於113平方米（1,220平方英尺）的窗型大小，讓人聯想到1974年的作品 ''4096色''  。雖然藝術家並未收取費用，不過光是材料和製作的費用就高達37萬歐元（506,000美元）。這些費用透過募款由1,000多人的捐款支付。<ref>[http://www.spiegel.de/international/zeitgeist/0,1518,502271,00.html Cologne Cathedral Gets New Stained-Glass Window] {{Wayback|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/zeitgeist/0,1518,502271,00.html |date=20110219160705 }} ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Der_Spiegel Der Spiegel]'', August 27, 2007</ref> 當時主教Joachim Meisner沒有參加彩色玻璃窗的正式揭幕；表示他較偏好具象地呈現基督徒烈士的方式，並說李希特的設計更適合出現在[[清真寺|清真寺]]或其他禱告殿。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/09/magazine/09pixelated.html?_r=1&ref=magazine&oref=slogin|title=Pixelated Stained Glass|last=Fortini|first=Amanda|date=2007-12-09|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2008-01-12|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2019-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029183021/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/09/magazine/09pixelated.html?_r=1&ref=magazine&oref=slogin|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.welt.de/politik/article1148224/Gerhard_Richter_weist_Meisner-Kritik__zurueck_.html Gerhard Richter weist Meisners Kritik zurück] {{Wayback|url=http://www.welt.de/politik/article1148224/Gerhard_Richter_weist_Meisner-Kritik__zurueck_.html |date=20071214231830 }}, ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Die_Welt Die Welt]'', 31 August 2007.</ref><ref>[http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,2754061,00.html Window by Artist Gerhard Richter Unveiled at Cologne Cathedral] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,2754061,00.html |date=20110803060218 }}, ''[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deutsche_Welle Deutsche Welle]'', 27 August 2007</ref> 雖然藝術家自稱為無神論者或“偏天主教徒”，不過李希特的三個孩子與他第三任妻子後來都在科隆大教堂受洗。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newyorker.com/arts/critics/artworld/2008/05/12/080512craw_artworld_schjeldahl |title=Peter Schjeldahl, "Many-colored Glass: Gerhard Richter and Sigmar Polke do windows, ''The New Yorker'', May 12, 2008. |accessdate=2017-01-27 |archive-date=2012-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114072827/http://www.newyorker.com/arts/critics/artworld/2008/05/12/080512craw_artworld_schjeldahl |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 展覽 ==
Richter first began exhibiting in Düsseldorf in 1963. Richter had his first gallery solo show in 1964 at Galerie Schmela in Düsseldorf. Soon after, he had exhibitions in [[慕尼黑|Munich]] and [[柏林|Berlin]] and by the early 1970s exhibited frequently throughout Europe and the United States. In 1966, [[Bruno_Bischofberger|Bruno Bischofberger]] was the first to show Richter's works outside Germany. Richter's first retrospective took place at the Kunsthalle Bremen in 1976 and covered works from 1962 to 1974. A traveling retrospective at Düsseldorf's Kunsthalle in 1986 was followed in 1991 by a retrospective at the [[泰特美術館|Tate Gallery]], London. In 1993 he received a major touring retrospective "Gerhard Richter: Malerei 1962–1993" curated by Kasper König, with a three volume catalogue edited by Benjamin Buchloch. This exhibition containing 130 works carried out over the course of thirty years, was to entirely reinvent Richter's career.

Richter became known to a U.S. audience in 1990, when the [[圣路易斯艺术博物馆|Saint Louis Art Museum]] circulated ''Baader-Meinhof (October 18, 1977)'', a show that that was later seen at the Lannan Foundation in Marina del Rey, California.<ref>Christopher Knight (April 6, 2002),[http://articles.latimes.com/2002/apr/06/entertainment/et-knight6/2 A Brush With Pop – A MOMA retrospective on Gerhard Richter might make you wrongly think he's a Conceptual painter.] {{Wayback|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2002/apr/06/entertainment/et-knight6/2 |date=20120715032904 }}</ref> Richter's first North American retrospective was in 1998 at the [[安大略美术馆|Art Gallery of Ontario]] and at the [[芝加哥现代美术馆|Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago]]. In 2002, a 40-year retrospective of Richter's work was held at the [[現代藝術博物館|Museum of Modern Art]], New York, and traveled to The [[芝加哥藝術博物館|Art Institute of Chicago]], the [[旧金山现代艺术博物馆|San Francisco Museum of Modern Art]], and the Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden, Washington, D.C. He has participated in several international art shows, including the [[威尼斯双年展|Venice Biennale]] (1972, 1980, 1984, 1997 and 2007), as well as [[卡塞尔文献展|Documenta]] V (1972), VII (1982), VIII (1987), IX (1992), and X (1997).{{Fact|date=October 2011}} In 2006, an exhibition at the [[盖蒂中心|Getty Center]] connected the landscapes of Richter to the Romantic pictures of [[卡斯帕·大衛·弗雷德里希|Caspar David Friedrich]], showing that both artists "used abstraction, expansiveness, and emptiness to express transcendent emotion through painting."<ref>[http://www.getty.edu/art/exhibitions/friedrich_richter/ "From Caspar David Friedrich to Gerhard Richter: German Paintings from Dresden"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.getty.edu/art/exhibitions/friedrich_richter/ |date=20120702052728 }}, October 5, 2006 – April 29, 2007 at the Getty Center</ref>

The Gerhard Richter Archive was established in cooperation with the artist in 2005 as an institute of the [[德累斯顿国家艺术收藏馆|Staatliche Kunstsammlungen Dresden]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gerhard-richter-archiv.de/ |title=www.gerhard-richter-archiv.de |accessdate=2020-09-18 |archive-date=2006-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060813111835/http://www.gerhard-richter-archiv.de/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

